49. Si puteal multa] The meaning of this line has been much disputed. It means something that the man should not do ; but what? ‘ Puteal Libonis ' was the place in the Forum Romanum where money-lenders did their business, as is generally believed. (Hor. S. ii. 6. 35, “Roscius orabat sibi adesses ad Puteal cras.”) It would seem then that the man whipped the Puteal severely, which may be, overreached the people who did business with him, being himself up to the tricks of trade (cautus). ,
